Hello Assi,
&nbsp;
Good Day!
&nbsp;
For your first query, the app packs the products based on the product weight and dimensions (if available) in to one of the packages enabled in. the Packaging Settings.
&nbsp;
If based on the configured weights (either the Box Max weight or total weight of the products as configured in Shopify), the app canoot pack all the items in to a single package, then it will split the order into 2 packages.
&nbsp;
Please refer to Box Packing Method and how it works here - https://www.pluginhive.com/knowledge-base/pack-products-optimally-and-save-shipping-costs-with-shopify-fedex-app/#box-packing
&nbsp;
Regarding the rates on checkout, when Saturday Delivery option is enabled in the app (Settings &gt; Account Settings &gt; Saturday Delivery), Saturday Delivery rates will be shown on checkout for the applicable services.
&nbsp;
To check the cases further, could you please share the following details -&nbsp;
  Screenshot of the complete transaction from the checkout of your store in which the products added in cart and the address provided are clearly visible along with the rates returned by the app. We will replicate the same transaction from our end and check the case further.  Correct One Rate available for Overnight services available on your FedEx account on fedex.com by using the exact same transaction details (ship from, ship to address, package weight and FedEx box). This will help us in verify the rates returned from the app for your cases.  &nbsp;
Awaiting your response.
&nbsp;
Thanks and Regards,
Touseef
Team PluginHive

